post_text: Thursday, September 13, was a beautiful night celebrating the Latin culture and young Latinos in the city of Newark pursuing their dreams through education. The North Ward Center hosted their 38th Annual Latino Scholarship dinner honoring five recipients, two of them were Alumni from Robert Treat Academy. To Genesis Chalmers and Jason Quinones, congratulations and may you continue to grow and succeed.

post_text: Check out this video of the Class of 2018 marching on the stepping stone to end their journey at RTA and to start a new one. On September 21st, RTA’s current Eighth grade will begin to lay down their stepping stones for their journey to high school starting with Interview Day. High School Representatives from Rhode Island to Virginia will travel to speak with our students to pick their brains and see why their high schools would benefit from our students attending their institution.

post_text:
#TBT
Four years ago Sebastian Santiago became the first recipient of the James A. Pinaire Scholarship. With this scholarship, Sebastian has been able to attend an all-boys boarding school in Pennsylvania, Church Farm. He has a GPA of 3.2, is taking an AP classes, and is part of the Track and Baseball team. Sebastian will be in his senior year at the end of this month and has taken the responsibility of being an RA (Resident Assistant) at his dorm. Due to the support of the Pinaire family and all who have generously donated, Sebastian will be the first Pinaire Scholarship recipient to go to college and be part of the Class of 2019. We wish Sebastian the best of luck on his senior year. Help push RTA students to continue to achieve greatness by contributing to the James A. Pinaire scholarship. Also remember our 5th Annual Golf Outing, which all proceeds raised will go to the James A. Pinaire Scholarship Fund, will be held on August 20th.

https://app.eventcaddy.com/events/robert-treat-academy-golf-outing

5th Annual RTA Golf Outing has been rescheduled to Tuesday, October 16th. We will follow the same schedule of activities for that day.

Visit our Golf outing web page on details for RTA's Fifth Annual Golf Outing.

All proceeds raised will go to the James A. Pinaire Scholarship Fund. This fund was established in memory of James, a beloved teacher who passed away in 2014, to help the families of RTA graduates earn scholarships towards their high school tuition.

post_text:
Bookmark Book Fair: Nov. 14-18
Our goal is that each student goes home with at least one book this year. Books for every interest and every grade level including popular, relevant, and current titles will be available.
Parents: please support your child’s interest in reading. Book Fair dates for both campuses are November 14 to 18 (Monday through Friday) with evening browsing time on November 16 before and after each school’s Thanksgiving play.
